<TEXT>
czechoslovakias new ambassador to the united 
states has an early form of leukemia and is trying to decide 
whether to remain in this country or return to her own the 
washington post said in its wednesday editions 
its not that we dont have good doctors at home ambassador 
rita klimova told the newspaper but we dont have the ability to 
protect patients from infection that requires a high degree of 
sophistication in the hospitals 
the ambassador who assumed her diplomatic post five months ago 
said her government will pay her medical bills but she is 
concerned about the finances and does not want to run up a big tab 
she said her decision on whether to stay in the united states 
will depend on finding treatment that fits in with someones 
research plans 
ms klimova became ill in may but the leukemia diagnosis is 
recent the newspaper said 
leukemia is a form of cancer of the bloodcell forming system 
though the disease once was considered invariably fatal treatment 
has improved dramatically in recent decades and years and complete 
remissions may be obtained for some types 
