<TEXT>
here is a look at how a 100 billion spending 
cut would be triggered by the grammrudman law and what it would 
mean 
how it works 
the white houses office of management and budget estimated 
monday that the fiscal 1991 deficit will hit 1688 billion or 
2314 billion if the savings and loan bailout is counted between 
now and oct 1 the start of the new fiscal year omb will 
monitor any new laws that affect spending or government revenue 
collections and take them into account if the projected deficit 
exceeds 74 billion on oct 1 10 billion above the target 
spending is cut temporarily by whatever amount is needed to reduce 
the shortfall to 64 billion the cuts take effect permanently on 
oct 15 
savings and loan rescue spending is included in the deficit 
calculations under current law but many in congress and the bush 
administration want to exclude those costs 
distribution of cuts 
50 percent to defense 50 percent to domestic programs but 
portions are exempt in full or in part 
defense about onethird of the 300 billion defense budget is 
exempt from grammrudman cuts because it has already been committed 
to longterm contracts of the remaining amount the law allows the 
president to exempt personnel costs such as salaries 
he chose not to exempt personnel last year if he made the same 
choice this time according to omb this could mean dismissal of 
about 1 million troops about half of the activeduty force 
layoffs or dismissals of up to half the militarys 11 million 
civilian employees and a cut in weapon acquisition programs such 
as reducing the request for major new naval ships from 15 to 11 
if personnel costs were exempted remaining programs would be 
slashed by 413 percent this would mean that the amount of flight 
time for aircraft and steaming time for ships would be cut by half 
and about 80 percent of the militarys civilian workers could lose 
their jobs 
domestic completely exempt from cuts are interest on the 
national debt social security and several federal retirement and 
disability programs several lowincome programs including food 
stamps medicaid and child nutrition aid and many veterans 
programs 
several other programs can be cut only partially cuts in 
medicare and some health programs for veterans and migrants are 
limited to 2 percent reductions there are also special rules for 
support payments to farmers and for guaranteed student loans 
spending on those programs subject to the full brunt of the cuts 
would be reduced by 384 percent according to omb that could mean 
a oneyear delay in hazardous waste cleanups at energy department 
sites elimination of vaccines for polio measles and other 
diseases for 1 million children a 20 percent cut for fbi 
investigations into organized crime and prevention of government 
plans to upgrade airline security overseas 
duration of cuts 
by law they remain in effect for the entire fiscal year once 
oct 15 passes but permanent grammrudman cuts have been 
rolled back before most recently just last fall 
</TEXT>
