the chilly water sapped most of my energy in the first two 
hours storch said he plans to swim about 17 miles a day and end 
the week at the statue of liberty in new york harbor 
twenty million people live work or play on or near the sound 
swim organizers said the waterway extends from new york harbor to 
the southwestern tip of rhode island 
herm hannah of the long island sound taskforce said it once was 
an important commercial fishing area where beachgoers could take a 
dip without getting a booster shot first 
unfortunately it has also been a dumping ground hannah 
said skip storch is going to highlight the good things he sees 
and try to make us very much aware what needs to be done to keep 
this sound clean and usable 
terry backer of the long island soundkeeper fund said ignoring 
cleanup efforts could be costly 
the coastal environment for rhode island connecticut and new 
york is the source of billions of dollars of revenue he said 
when people feel the waters are open sewers were going to 
lose that revenue 
it wasnt the first time storch has embarked on a long swim to 
heighten awareness about water pollution 
last summer he swam from atlantic city nj to new york harbor 
and the summer before he swam down the hudson river from albany 
ny to the statue of liberty 
