<TEXT>
israels supreme court today overturned 
emergency regulations by housing minister ariel sharon to speed the 
construction of homes for thousands of soviet immigrants 
the threejudge panel ruled sharon could have sought approval 
for the programs from parliament instead of using the emergency 
powers 
it was the first time the court challenged the governments use 
of such regulations which date from israels 1948 independence war 
up to 150000 soviet immigrants are expected to arrive this 
year tent cities are springing up across the country as part of 
protests by israelis who say subsidies for immigrants are driving 
up rents and pricing others out of the housing market 
sharon who also serves as cabinet coordinator of immigration 
had asked to use emergency regulations to allow the purchase of 
3000 prefabricated homes either locally or abroad the cabinet 
approved it july 1 
there is no doubt that this is a revolutionary decision 
said moshe negbi a legal expert for the hebrew daily newspaper 
hadashot 
he said the procedure for emergency powers was introduced during 
war in 1948 when there was a fear the knesset or parliament could 
not always be convened because of the fighting 
for the first time the supreme court clearly says that the 
government must not use these radical powers when there is no 
problem in convening the parliament negbi said it must not 
get around the parliament and adopt its authority 
under the emergency regulations the cabinet authorized the 
prefabricated housing units to be set up near nine israeli towns 
most in the galilee in the north and in the southern negev desert 
some politicians expressed fear that sharon would try to take 
undemocratic actions assuming powers delegated to planning 
councils and zoning boards sharon was accused as defense minister 
in 1982 of concealing military plans from the government that led 
to the armys invasion of lebanon 
the high court panel issued its ruling after a liberal 
legislator abraham poraz of the shinui party appealed sharons 
use of emergency regulations 
in his appeal poraz argued sharon used emergency regulations at 
a time when the knesset was debating the housing crisis last week 
the knesset passed a law that shortened housing license procedures 
emergency regulations are an antidemocratic act that 
should be used only in difficult exceptional situations when 
there is no other choice poraz said on israel army radio 
the government argued in its court response that emergency 
regulations were needed to ease the housing crisis created by the 
mass influx of soviet jews 
according to figures submitted by the government israels 
20000 available rental apartments will be filled by the end of 
september 
