a jubilant chancellor helmut kohl said 
today that he and mikhail s gorbachev have solved all practical 
problems in the way of german unification and that elections for an 
allgerman parliament are expected on dec 2 
kohl met with reporters a day after returning from a twoday 
trip to the soviet union where he and the soviet president 
announced gorbachev had dropped his objections to nato membership 
for a united germany 
the soviet objections had been the most significant obstacle to 
unification 
the practical problems which lay before us on the way to 
german unity have been solved kohl said 
he said joint german elections were expected dec 2 but whether 
east germany merges with the west before or after elections had to 
be decided by east berlin 
he also reiterated his position that the capital of a united 
germany must be decided by the new parliament 
east german prime minister lothar de maiziere who is pushing 
for berlin over bonn as united germanys capital has said the 
capital must be stipulated in a unification treaty now in 
preparation 
kohl said that during his visit he had offered no specific 
economic aid to the soviets but he emphasized that gorbachev needs 
financial help if his program of economic restructuring is to 
succeed 
