<TEXT>
israels supreme court on tuesday overturned 
housing minister ariel sharons use of emergency regulations to 
speed up construction of housing for thousands of soviet immigrants 
sharon was also dealt another blow as tourism minister gideon 
patt opposed a second crash program for the immigrants under which 
the soviet jews would live temporarily in hotels and youth hostels 
the threejudge supreme court panel ruled sharon could have 
sought approval from the parliament or knesset instead of using 
emergency powers 
tent camps are springing up across the country as a protest by 
israelis who say subsidies for immigrants are driving up rents and 
pricing others out of the housing market 
more than 63000 soviet jews have arrived since 1989 and the 
