the subcommittee that reporting the provision of the dingellwaxman 
bill is neither necessary nor feasible 
he said he also opposes another provision that would require 
more devices to undergo more intensive scrutiny even though they 
were similar to devices already on the market he said this 
provision would lengthen product review times raise health care 
costs and impede the introduction of new technologies to the 
market 
