that navy doctors who provide medical care for congress members 
were negligent in john easts care hourihan said that if 
physicians had administered a simple blood test as early as april 
1983 they would have detected easts thyroid deficiency 
hypothyroidism occurs when the thyroid gland fails to produce 
the hormone needed to regulate the bodys metabolism 
hourihan noted that for 52 years east had overcome such 
obstacles as partial paralysis by polio his brothers suicide and 
parents deaths he pointed out that east was a lawyer and 
political science professor at east carolina university before 
being tapped to run for the senate in 1980 by the national 
congressional club the political organization of sen jesse helms 
rnc 
east lapsed into a coma when he was admitted to bethesda naval 
medical center in april 1985 not long after he regained 
consciousness east tried to kill himself by ramming a chair leg 
down his throat a manifestation of the psychotic state induced by 
extreme hypothyroidism 
easts condition was diagnosed when a hospital resident ordered 
the appropriate blood test 
hourihan said that whether or not easts thinking abilities 
actually were damaged after his metabolism was returned to normal 
the senator believed they were beyond repair hourihan said the 
fact or the belief created in east an irresistible impulse to kill 
himself attributable to navy doctors failure to treat the senator 
according to medical standards 
hourihan faulted rear adm freeman cary head of the 
congressional medical office who hourihan said treated east for a 
myriad of symptoms over two years 
dr cary treated each of these problems separately he never 
put them together and tried to evaluate them hourihan said 
but government defense attorney oring contended that mrs easts 
attorneys failed to show easts suicide was inevitable and a direct 
result of the late diagnosis of his thyroid disorder 
oring showed a portion of a onehour cable television interview 
with the senator in may 1986 a month before his death in which a 
poised and articulate east discussed national politics 
