the chiefs said i hope this will kick the federal government in 
the pants and get them moving to do something positive 
oka was quiet tuesday quebecs native affairs minister john 
ciaccia was expected to return for negotiations but did not arrive 
the mohawks announced late tuesday they have called in lawyers 
who specialize in native affairs to help with negotiations 
an indian statement said william kunstler of new york a human 
rights lawyer and constitutional expert and stanley cohen a new 
york civil rights lawyer will also join the oka mohawks 
