pointe military base in montreal on standby in the stalemate 
an armed forces officer who visited the base told the montreal 
gazette on monday he saw convoys of military trucks armed 
personnel carriers communications vehicles and antitank weapons 
capt alain lefrancois quebec public affairs officer for the 
department of national defense said tuesday soldiers would not 
intervene unless asked to do so by the provincial government 
royal canadian mounted police officers from across canada also 
moved into the area to act as reserves for quebec police in case 
fighting flares up again 
