red cross which has set up a relief fund 
chan said the consulate was receiving calls about every 10 
minutes from anxious filipinos with relatives in the devastated 
area 
unfortunately we dont have the names chan said 
the americares relief organization in new caanan conn had 
supplies and volunteers in the philippines before the quake 
spokesman steve norman said 
if a disaster had to occur in a place where we had to get to 
quickly the philippines was an ideal place norman said 
explaining that the group had been working for some time there with 
the knights of malta a roman catholic humanitarian group 
an americares plane carrying medical supplies was to leave from 
memphis tenn early wednesday norman said 
the organization recently sent supplies to iran after the 
devastating earthquake that reportedly killed 40000 people 
norman said donations have been generous but said people may be 
tapped out due to other recent disasters 
phone lines to the philippines were jammed monday by an 
unusually large number of calls american telephone amp telegraph co 
spokesman randy shields said in san francisco the company 
following its policy in disasters allowed more calls going out of 
the philippines than coming in shields said 
