the cuban foreign ministry in its statement released by prensa 
latina said the 12 cubans were detained for questioning in an 
investigation into what the cuban government described as a 
planned provocation around the czechoslovak embassy according to 
prensa latina 
it said the cubans would not face prosecution because they had 
left the embassy voluntarily and would be allowed to return to 
their homes upon completion of the investigation 
however the statement indicated that they would not be allowed 
to leave cuba 
the elements who enter any western embassy if they do not 
merit asylum will never leave this country in that manner the 
statement said 
a czechoslovak foreign ministry official jindrich opava said 
by telephone tuesday that he had no details on the circumstances of 
the asylumseekers leaving 
seven of the 12 cubans took several diplomats hostage monday at 
the czechoslovak embassy czechoslovak television reported later 
that all the diplomats were released unharmed notimex the mexican 
government news agency reported from havana that the seven then 
shouted out a window they would blow up the embassy if their demand 
for a plane to the united states was not met 
cuba and czechoslovakia had been close allies until last falls 
democratic upheaval toppled pragues hardline communist leaders 
cuban president fidel castro is one of a handful of surviving 
hardline marxist leaders after a reformist trend swept eastern 
europe last year 
castro in his first official statement on the matter called 
the asylumseekers antisocial elements encouraged by czechoslovak 
diplomats the czechoslovak newspaper lidova demokracie said 
monday 
ramon cernuda an anticastro cuban human rights activist in 
miami said that among the asylum seekers identified by the cuban 
government were three noted dissidents 
novoa ponce mari becerra and cabrera puentes had been 
imprisoned last year after they formed a group to promote artistic 
freedom cernuda said 
it was not immediately known whether they were among those who 
left the czechoslovak embassy 
