had helped finance the pageant of the antebellum days and whose 
production was the regions signature the land of cotton 
boll weevil coming fast the peoples ledger warned coffee 
countys farmers in 1910 the census that year recorded a bumper 
cotton crop 25207 bales in 1916 a year after the weevil 
arrived only 1500 bales were ginned in enterprise 
elsewhere it was no different in 1921 the boll weevil which 
devours cotton bolls and buds went through 30 percent of the 
souths crop 
a folk song tried to make light of the pest 
first time i saw the boll weevil he was standin on the 
square 
next time i saw the boll weevil he had his whole family there 
they was lookin for a home 
just lookin for a home 
