the farmers and to new farmers getting into it theres been a 
big expansion in acreage 
while us cotton production rose only 10 percent between 1980 
and 89 from 111 million to 122 million bales north carolinas 
nearly tripled from 52000 to 141000 bales 
in north and south carolina the boll weevil has been 
eradicated as an economic pest of cotton the national cotton 
council said in a 1989 report 
further results in the southwest arizona and southern 
california eradication program are equally impressive weevil 
populations fell approximately 95 percent in the first year the 
containment program also is working in texas the council said 
referring to the high plains growing area near lubbock usda also 
lists virginia within the eradicated zone 
is the weevil finally on the run then as the eradication effort 
continues in georgia northern florida and southern alabama 
