money and manpower to do its job right 
our coasts deserve a better defense than they are getting from 
false economizing said the centers michael weber 
the center said better radar used in other parts of the world 
could be used in domestic ports for less than the cost of a 
cleaning up a goodsized spill exxon has spent 2 billion on the 
valdez cleanup 
in valdez the coast guard cut the power on its radar and 
reduced crew sizes for budget reasons the exxon valdez was off the 
screen when it crashed foreign ports have radar that beeps an 
alarm if a ship strays from its channel in another costcutting 
move the coast guard cut out vessel traffic systems in new york 
and new orleans the system used in five ocean ports allows 
