the existing vessel traffic services in the us are far from 
state of the art said richard townsend who did the study for 
the center for marine conservation much better systems currently 
are available using offtheshelf technology that is vastly 
superior to that currently used by the coast guard 
in the private sector 20 oil companies formed the petroleum 
industry response organization last year the group would set up 
five regional centers covering 24 coastal states that would act as 
gigantic fire houses with booms skimmers and oil dispersants 
but the organization is waiting for congress before it buys any 
equipment 
the void that existed when the exxon valdez had its accident 
still exists as far as cleanup is concerned said retired adm 
john costello who heads the group we dont own any ships or any 
booms yet 
