contribute 430 million in new capital in exchange for 70 percent 
of the common stock in the restructured company previously the 
two had agreed to inject 400 million and get 75 percent of the new 
company 
the founding thompson familys share of the company would be 
reduced form 65 percent to about 5 percent 
bondholders would get the additional shares upping their 
holdings to about 25 percent of the new company 
besides the increased stock the most senior bondholders would 
receive 57 in cash for each 1000 of the bonds they currently 
hold no cash was included in the previous agreement 
other changes include increasing principal amounts of new 
securities and common stock swapped for the old debt in exchange 
the maturity dates are lengthened and interest rates lowered 
