<TEXT>
nynex corp neither funded nor supported a 
subsidiarys annual florida parties that featured call girls and 
clients the chairman of the telephone company said tuesday 
the annual miami parties which occurred between 1984 and 1988 
were attended by employees of materiel enterprises co which at 
the time was nynexs unregulated purchasing arm and about 30 
suppliers 
the parties reportedly featured awards for the most perverted 
partygoer and to the man who procured the most women 
at a news conference nynex chairman william ferguson called the 
activities sophomoric and repugnant he said none of the 
activities that were investigated were sponsored by the company 
none were paid for by the company none took place on company 
time 
an internal 1988 nynex investigation of the events resulted in 
two employees being fired and six others being disciplined for 
violating nynexs code of business conduct 
a fired nynex consultant who had no dealings with the parties 
told the wall street journal that suppliers who attended and paid 
for the parties saw their business increase by 67 percent while 
those who didnt saw an increase of only about 35 percent 
ferguson said those figures were misleading and said there was 
no evidence that any supplier ever benefited due to the parties 
he also said the nynex investigation showed that employees who 
attended the parties paid their own way he said some offered 
canceled checks as proof while others said they paid cash 
materiel enterprises activities have become a key issue in the 
companys pending request to new york regulators for a record 
9197 million rate increase 
the federal communications commission in february ordered fines 
totaling 14 million against the companys new york telephone co 
and new england telephone and telegraph co subsidiaries because of 
1185 million in alleged overcharges made to the two units by 
materiel enterprises 
materiel enterprises which was formed in 1983 to provide 
equipment and services to the telephone companies allegedly 
engaged in a series of transactions with the two aimed at 
increasing nynexs overall profit at customer expense 
the fcc also ordered the two telephone subsidiaries to refund 
about 35 million to customers nynex has appealed the fine and 
refund order 
