785 percent as the discount lost 2 basis points to 760 percent 
yields on sixmonth bills auctioned monday were 787 percent as the 
discount fell 4 basis points to 748 percent yields on oneyear 
bills fell to 786 percent as the discount lost 2 basis points to 
734 percent 
a basis point is onehundredth of a percentage point the yield 
is the annualized return on an investment in a treasury bill the 
discount is the percentage that bills are selling below the face 
value which is paid at maturity 
